                                        <fixVersion>2.1.6</fixVersion>
                    <fixVersion>2.2.0 rc1</fixVersion>
                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>1</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14543972" author="benedict" created="Thu, 14 May 2015 16:38:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Basically we don&apos;t wait for reads to complete before freeing the data in the exceptional case of truncate. I have merged the two paths, so that they follow the same protocol (of waiting).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14567605" author="iamaleksey" created="Mon, 1 Jun 2015 17:22:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The newly added &lt;tt&gt;discard&lt;/tt&gt; &lt;tt&gt;ArrayList&lt;/tt&gt; is not being used by anything. I assume something&apos;s not right here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14569441" author="benedict" created="Tue, 2 Jun 2015 17:14:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That was erroneously left present. Originally I had intended to collect the memtables to discard at once (thereby only issuing one barrier for all of them). Since typically there isn&apos;t more than one, and the efficiency isn&apos;t dramatic, I opted to just immediately reclaim as that improved clarity.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve pushed an updated version &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/belliottsmith/cassandra/tree/9388-2.1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; (with equivalent branches for each mainline)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14569461" author="iamaleksey" created="Tue, 2 Jun 2015 17:25:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
